	(text "TODO:\n1. Verify if the DT1240A-08LP3810Q is a good ESD IC\n2. Add 2-pin JST connectors to match the emitter JST so they can easily be plugged in without havign to modify the wire ends.\nflyback diode on input filter not needed as currents are very low\n3. Add a fuse to protect mosfet short circuit event (can happen if PWM inputs are either DC high or are driving at very high frequency)\n4. Change some of the footprints (resistors and caps) to SMD. (see Tobia's inductor kit and see if you can put those here as well)\n\nDisregarded circuit changes ideas:\n"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
